cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents a fast implementation of the Singular Value Thresholding (SVT) algorithm for matrix completion, which involves numerical computations and optimization. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper applies the SVT algorithm to matrix completion applications such as image recovery and movie recommendation system, which are common machine learning tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions image recovery as one of the matrix completion applications, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision and pattern recognition. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a recycling rank revealing randomized singular value decomposition (R4SVD) algorithm, which involves designing and analyzing algorithms for efficient matrix decomposition. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper employs a simulated annealing style cooling mechanism to adaptively adjust the low-rank approximation precision threshold, which may involve information-theoretic concepts such as entropy and mutual information.
